track_notes: You can park at the parking de lEspaul; the last part is a bit vertigo.
This is a 18km track. starting from le Col de lEspaul

Parking is ok at the Col de l Espaul.
This is the normal path to this summit when no snow.
The walk is not difficult, but you must no vertigo as the final crest looks hard, but it is not.
Just watch the weather forecast; if you are a good walker it will take 5 hours (up and down). Plenty room on summit for antenna (summit can be crowded).
